        "execSummary":  "Power capacity is emerging as the binding constraint on enterprise AI scaling, and this article reframes the infrastructure conversation around energy efficiency rather than raw GPU counts. For CIOs and enterprise architects planning AI factory investments, the message is clear: total cost of ownership must now incorporate power and cooling costs as primary variables, not afterthoughts. NVIDIA\u0027s 25x performance-per-watt claim for Blackwell NVL72 versus Hopper is a compelling headline, but enterprises should model actual workload profiles rather than rely on peak benchmark figures. This is also a strategic reminder that vendor lock-in risk is real ΓÇö optimizing deeply for one platform\u0027s efficiency stack creates switching costs if the competitive landscape shifts.",
