        "summary":  "CIOs are under pressure to accelerate AI adoption while managing risks that differ fundamentally from traditional technology due to AI\u0027s indeterminate outputs. The article examines how IT leaders use organizational structures, risk frameworks, and governance platforms to create \u0027healthy internal tensions\u0027 between innovation and compliance teams. Industry experts warn that speed without proper governance creates dangerous shadow AI use, while thoughtful maturity models enable secure, scalable experimentation.",
        "execSummary":  "This article captures the central governance dilemma facing enterprise AI leaders in 2026: moving too slowly cedes competitive ground while moving too fast creates uncontrolled risk exposure, particularly through shadow AI proliferating outside sanctioned channels. The finding that structured governance actually enables faster and safer scaling ΓÇö rather than slowing it ΓÇö is a critical message for boards and executive teams that frame oversight as friction. For customer-support leaders deploying AI agents, this translates directly: governance frameworks for agent behavior, escalation paths, and audit trails are not optional risk-management exercises but prerequisites for sustainable scale. The key caveat is that generic risk frameworks designed for traditional software often fail to account for AI\u0027s probabilistic nature, requiring purpose-built AI governance approaches.",
