        "summary":  "Columnist Thornton May argues that CIOs cannot solve AI adoption challenges by making systems simpler ΓÇö they must invest in genuine stakeholder education and compelling communication. A troubling statistic anchors the piece: 60% of organizations deploying generative AI provide no formal training to users. May advocates for \u0027knowledge pumping\u0027 paired with individualized executive education, effective data visualization, and narratives that connect AI to organizational mission rather than cost savings alone.",
