        "summary":  "The article argues that AI agents require fundamentally different infrastructure than traditional Kubernetes was designed for. While Kubernetes optimized for stateless, short-lived HTTP requests, agent workloads are long-running and stateful, demanding new compute patterns including rapid environment provisioning, durable state management, multi-agent coordination, and secure credential handling.",
