        "summary":  "The article examines why major AI companies like Anthropic, Google, and OpenAI are donating foundational technologies such as MCP and A2A protocols to open foundations. Rather than acts of altruism, these donations represent a strategic shift where competitive advantage moves from owning the models themselves to controlling the platforms where AI work naturally accumulates and integrates with enterprise systems.",
        "execSummary":  "The real AI battleground has shifted from model capability to platform control ΓÇö Anthropic, Google, and OpenAI are \u0027donating\u0027 protocols like MCP and A2A to open foundations not out of generosity but to establish gravitational pull around their enterprise integration surfaces. For senior enterprise leaders, this means platform and vendor lock-in is quietly being baked into AI infrastructure choices made today, often under the guise of open standards. The implication: enterprise architects need to scrutinize which company\u0027s ecosystem a given \u0027open\u0027 standard actually benefits before committing to it. Governance and interoperability planning must account for this strategic reality.",
